Polish Ruling Party Lead Narrows in Poll, Rzeczpospolita Reports

-- B y   M a c i e j   M a r t e w i c z
-- 
2011-09-15T05:09:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/polish-ruling-party-lead-narrows-in-poll-rzeczpospolita-reports.html
Support for  Civic Platform ,
Poland’s ruling party, fell to 44 percent from 47 percent two
weeks earlier, Rzeczpospolita newspaper reported, citing a Sept.
8 to Sept. 12 poll by GfK Polonia.  The Platform’s lead over Law & Justice narrowed as backing
for the biggest opposition party rose to 32 percent from 29
percent, the newspaper reported, citing a survey that questioned
972 Poles.  The Democratic  Left Alliance , also in the opposition, would
attract 11 percent of voters in Oct. 9 elections, according to
the poll. The Polish Peasants Party, the junior coalition
partner in government, had 4 percent support, the newspaper
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maciej Martewicz at 
 mmartewicz@bloomberg.net  